-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Sept 19
-- 
-- Fri Sep 19, 2014 01:27AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Sept 19 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Friday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Main shareholder of Bulgaria's Corporate Commercial Bank, Tsvetan Vassilev, said he would not seek to return to Bulgaria quickly after a Bulgarian court refused to lift his arrest warrant. Vassilev, who is awaiting an extradition procedure in Serbia, said he is under strong political pressure. (Presa, 24 Chasa, Trud, Capital Daily, Monitor, Sega) CAPITAL DAILY - State-controlled Bulgarian Energy Holding has decided to replace the executive director of nuclear plant Kozloduy Ivan Genov and appointed Dimitar Angelov on the post.  -- The European Bank for Reconstruction and Development cut its forecast for economic growth in Bulgaria for this year to 1.5 percent citing political instability and recent banking turmoil. (Capital Daily, Trud, Presa, Monitor, Sega)